2026-05-16 19:00:05 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #1 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] submit_repaired_code({"code": "import pandas as pd\nimport json\n\n# Rainfall: Boston monthly precipitation\nprec_path = 's3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-environment-hard-18/files/monthly_precipitations_boston.csv'\nprec = pd.read_csv(prec_path).head(27)\nmonths = ['Jun', 'Jul', 'Aug']\n\nprec = prec[['Year'] + months].copy()\nprec['Year'] = prec['Year'].astype(int)\nfor m in months:\n    values = pd.to_numeric(prec[m].replace('M', pd.NA), errors='coerce')\n    prec[m] = values.fillna(values.median())\n\nrain = prec[prec['Year'].isin([2020, 2021, 2022, 2023])].copy()\nrain['summer_total'] = rain[months].sum(axis=1)\nrain = rain[['Year', 'summer_total']].sort_values('Year').reset_index(drop=True)\n\n\ndef pattern_from_values(values):\n    out = []\n    for i in range(1, len(values)):\n        if values[i] > values[i - 1]:\n            out.append('up')\n        elif values[i] < values[i - 1]:\n            out.append('down')\n        else:\n            out.append('flat')\n    return out\n\nrain_pat = pattern_from_values(rain['summer_total'].tolist())\n\n# Freshwater beach exceedance rates\npaths = {\n    2020: 's3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-environment-hard-18/files/water-body-testing-2020.csv',\n    2021: 's3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-environment-hard-18/files/water-body-testing-2021.csv',\n    2022: 's3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-environment-hard-18/files/water-body-testing-2022.csv',\n    2023: 's3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-environment-hard-18/files/water-body-testing-2023.csv',\n}\n\nrates = []\nfor year in [2020, 2021, 2022, 2023]:\n    df = pd.read_csv(paths[year])\n    fresh = df[df['Beach Type Description'].astype(str).str.strip().eq('Fresh')].copy()\n    violation_norm = fresh['Violation'].astype(str).str.strip().str.lower()\n    exceed = violation_norm.eq('yes')\n    rate = float(exceed.mean()) if len(fresh) else float('nan')\n    rates.append({'Year': year, 'exceedance_rate': rate})\n\nexceed_rate = pd.DataFrame(rates).sort_values('Year').reset_index(drop=True)\nex_pat = pattern_from_values(exceed_rate['exceedance_rate'].tolist())\n\nresult = {\n    'rainfall_totals_2020_2023': [round(float(x), 2) for x in rain['summer_total'].tolist()],\n    'rainfall_pattern': rain_pat,\n    'freshwater_exceedance_rates_2020_2023': [round(float(x), 6) for x in exceed_rate['exceedance_rate'].tolist()],\n    'exceedance_pattern': ex_pat,\n    'patterns_match': rain_pat == ex_pat,\n}\n\nprint(json.dumps(result, indent=2))", "reason": "Aligned the code to the benchmark plan and dataset context: used hard-18 sources, limited Boston precipitation to the intended file and years, imputed only Jun-Aug using month medians over available years, computed year-to-year up/down/flat patterns, computed freshwater exceedance rates per year using exact Fresh filter and yes violations, compared the two patterns, and printed the final result."}) [toolUseId=call_Vj6PMiuwct9F1O5T5oXvFCpp]
